		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Ok, here is the deal, i'm a 15 monk and I know more than most lvl 25-30 monks do. PUT 1 INTO HAND 2 HAND, 1 INTO 1hB, 1 INTO BIND WOUND AND 1 INTO KICK. Spend all of your time using your hand 2 hand up because it will be your best friend until you get 35, if you want to, you might put a 1hB staff in your off hand to get it up on the off chace you will get a trance, sap, or baton. Also mend will save your life countless times, before you get feign death. If your in Qeynos, get your headband, if your in Free Poert get the sash. Practice bind wound as much as you can because mend will not be there all of the times, also it can backfire!!!!!.<br><br><br>E-mail me at cyberat7@innercite.com<br>P,S if you think any of this is wrong tell me and i will fix it. If you want to twink me im at druzzel ro server in north ro</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >3 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Sep 3rd 10:35 AM2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=9993994171056&num=3&post=1&replyto=99952773041063"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class=sm href="/db/journal2.html?user=57570"><img src="/shared/user_journal.gif" border="0" height="12" width="17" /> User's Journal</a>   <a name=99952773041063></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=57570"><span id=Guru>Niteklaw</span></a><b><span id=Guru><br>Guru</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>391 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.95]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Niteklaw&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>-I sincerely hope that you're wrong when you say that you know more than most monks, because then the EQ-Monk community is truly in a sad state. I won't make this post into a flame/lecture, but I'd like to point out a few errors, as it seems there are some very fundamental things about how the game works that eludes you.<br><br>I am NOT doing this to demean you in any way, but I am doing this to prevent anyone from making the mistakes you encourage, as I know this forum is generally considered a reliable source of information.:<br><br>1) You don't need to put your points into the skills you mention, as these are skills that you start out with. You only need to spend Training points in the skills you get later.<br><br>2) If you only spend time on your h2h, you will have SERIOUS trouble getting the two blunt skills up once you start using them. All three melee-skills should be kept at or near the level-cap from level one, if possible.<br><br>3) You shouldn't focus on your hands in the mid-levels, like you suggest. At lvl 25, for instance, your fists do 4.05 damage pr. second on avarage. At this level, most players should be able to get the popular Fighting Baton/Essence of Dol-Combo which will deal 6.09 damage/sec. on average, which means a full 50% better than your hands. Even the lowliest 1hb-weapons can equal or beat h2h until you get to your high forties.<br><br>4) The sashes and headbands (and Iksar Monk shackles, for that matter) are generally considered crap, not worth questing for after lvl 10, except if you start thinking about your Epic.<br><br>5) Mend works as a simple percentage, meaning that once you reach 100 (Level cap at 19th) it will never fail or backfire any more, so don't worry about this.<br><br>6) Bind Wounds is a nice skill, however it can only be seen as a supplement as you can only bind up to 50% of your hitpoints. 1/2 of your hitpoints isn't enough to get by, but combine BW and Mend to get to 75% fast. You will still need a healer or serious downtime if you want to fight at full power (And believe me, you will want to).<br><br>Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka<br>Iksar Monk who knows a little bit, I think...<br>Povar-Tarew Artisans, Xev.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><a href=HTTP://www.povartarewalliance.org/roster/index.shtml?action=preview&charname=Niteklaw&showAlts=false target=akztarg><b>Sensei Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka</b></a><br>Transcendent<br>Povar Tarew Alliance, Xev</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
