		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.70]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Corr&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Just a small add.&nbsp;&nbsp;Bind wound is VERY VERY USEFUL.  From about 1-40 , 90 percent of my leveling has been though soloing.  The trick is to bind wound up to half life , take off all your hp gear , then bind wound up to half again , put on your hp gear , and you will have gained an extra half a buble leaving you at 3 bubles of health.  Usually , this was enough for me to solo another mob.  When i hit my early 40s , my bind wound was alredy maxed , and when a monk hits 51 , his bind wound cap is removed.  So at 201 skill , a monk can bind wound up to 70% and at about 80 hp per bandage.  Currently using the bind/remove hp gear trick , i can bindwound up to 4 bubles of health.  This will usually be enough for me to solo low blue mobs even at 53.<br><br>P.S. best to remove that "plez twink me kthnx" message on the bottom of the post in the future.  Begging will drop your respectability points big time.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Corr<br>60 Grandmaster of the celestial fists<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31645" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31645</a><br></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3&post=1